            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.68-69_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">68</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Tuesday</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear John,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am afraid that I am in trouble on the records. I am not a resident of California and it seems impossible to get a loan. I have no personal property here (my car is in Kansas <del/><add>C</add>ity) and I can not get a loan on my signature. This comes as quite a blow because my credit is very good in Kansas City and Columbia. If I were home I could borrow as much as a thousand dollars but this is not at home.</p>
                
                <p>I hate to ask you but can you loan me $200 at 10% interest? I would pay back the loan in twelve installments of $18.35 each if I am not able to pay it back sooner. I certainly think that I shall be able to it back in much less tha<del/><add>n</add> a year for I will be paying on it as money comes in on the records. But if business is slower than we expect I can handle the monthly pay<del>em</del><add>me</add>nts easily from the money my parents are sending me to live on.</p>
                
                <p>In case something should happen to <del>b</del><add>m</add>e before it is paid back I have a $5000 insurance policy. I haven't paid enough in on it to borrow any amount on it but it is paid up.</p>
                
                <p>I am very sorry to have to ask you to loan me any money. I was h<del>p</del><add>o</add>ping that I wouldn't ha<del>e</del><add>v</add>e to borrow in order to finish the records, but it didn't occur to me that I couldn't borrow money out here.</p>
                
                <p>The pressings are ordered and I am supposed to pick up the finished albums Thursday. I will send you twenty five or so for you to autograph as soon as you return them to me we will be ready to mail them out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Sandy</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial"><add><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></add> (over)</note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.68-69_0002"/>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>If you can lend me the money, please send the necessary papers and I will sign them and <del>t</del><add>r</add>eturn them to you. If you don't have enough to spare I will try to raise the money from some friends here.</p>
                </postscript>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
